<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kuerten Wins Hamburg Masters Series Final  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
BERLIN, May 21 (Xinhua) -- Brazilian Gustavo Kuerten won the
Hamburg Masters Series on Sunday with a 6-4, 5-7, 6-4, 5-7, 7-6
win over Russian Marat Safin in 3 hours 51 minutes.
</P>
<P>
The fifth seed from Brazil, who had lost his three previous
matches against Safin, kept his cool under fire from the 20-year-
old's heavy artillery and held on to win the final set tiebreak 7-
3 on the first of three match points, according to reports
reaching here.
</P>
<P>
Twelfth seed Safin, who had won 17 of his last 18 matches,
troubled his opponent with heavy groundstrokes. But the towering
20-year-old struggled to get his first serves in and lacked
composure at crucial moments.
</P>
<P>
Kuerten, who lost last weekend's Rome Masters final to Magnus
Norman, shot to fame by triumphing as a complete outsider at
Roland-Garros in 1997.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
