<DOCNO> XIE20000522.0011 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-05-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Food Output, Sale Drop in Romania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, May 22 (Xinhua) -- Romania's sales of foodstuffs
dropped by 30.4 percent in the first two months of this year
against the same period of 1999, exceptions being vegetable oil,
margarine, beer and tobacco, the official Rompres news agency
quoted Monday data of the National Statistics Commission as
reporting.
</P>
<P>
The plunge in consumption was the result of price rises and
attracted a shrinkage in the output of the respective industries.
</P>
<P>
Romania's per capita consumption of meat dwindled to 30 kg from
45 kg in recent years, prompting negative effects on the
population's health.
</P>
<P>
The activity of nearly 30 percent of Romania's food processing
firms is now at a standstill, with many of them facing bankruptcy.
</P>
<P>
The Romanian industry of canned vegetable and fruit and the
sugar industry account for a meager 25 percent of the domestic
demands, with imports being higher than the domestic output.
</P>
<P>
Increased taxation for the 441 food companies resulted in price
rises for vegetable oil, sugar, milk, meat and bread amid lower
personal income, according to the National Statistics Commission.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
