<HEADLINE> Cuban Vice President Meets German Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"One of the most important things for improving these relations
is to know Cuba's reality", said Lage, who met on Sunday Germany's
Minister of Economic Cooperation and Development, Heidemarie
Wieczorek-Zeul.
</P>
<P>
"We held a very open and frank dialogue concerning economic
cooperation, development projects, relations between Germany and
Cuba", he said.
</P>
<P>
He considered Wieczorek-Zeul's visit "very important for Cuba's
relationship with Germany and EU".
</P>
<P>
The Minister's visit is the first of a German official of this
level to the island.
</P>
<P>
Due to political differences, Cuba is the only nation of Latin
American and the Caribbean that hasn't signed a cooperation accord
with European Union.
</P>
<P>
Cuba renounced in April its eventual adhering to the EU-ACP (
Africa, Caribbean, Pacific) Covenant whereby EU grants trade
advantages to nations of these three regions. 
</P>
