<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ethiopia Not to Occupy Eritrean Territory: PM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, May 22 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopian Prime Minister Meles
Zenawi said on Monday that Ethiopian troops' recent incursions
deep into western Eritrea were only part of a military strategy
without any intention to occupy Eritrean territory.
</P>
<P>
"We have no intention in anyway of infringing on Eritrean
sovereignty. That was not the issue. That is not the issue, and
that will not be the issue," said Meles when briefing resident
African diplomats here.
</P>
<P>
"That Ethiopia is land-locked is no surprise; it is not a new
thing to us. We knew what we were going into then. We have no
regrets about that", the prime minister said.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopia was the first country to accept the result of the
independence referendum in Eritrea, a former province of Ethiopia,
he recalled.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopia, as it has always been, is ready to go to the
negotiating table, and start dialogue on substantive issues, said
Meles.
</P>
<P>
But "the ball is in Eritrea's court. We had to start from
where we left off, which is the Algiers proximity talks," he
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
