<HEADLINE> Ethiopian Troops Capture More Eritrean Land </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, May 22 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopian troops, continuing
their attacks on Eritrean troops for 11 days running, have
captured another piece of land in southern Eritrean called
Kohain, an official statement said Monday.
</P>
<P>
The Office of the Government Spokesperson said that Ethiopian
defence forces have in their assault Sunday evening inflicted
heavy losses on two Eritrean brigades stationed in Kohain and
controlled the entire area and the town of Maimine, which is
located in southern Eritrea.
</P>
<P>
Referring to the situation in the eastern warfront of Bure, the
office said that Ethiopian defence forces attacked and captured
Eritrean surveillance posts.
</P>
<P>
The Eritrean army launched a counter-offensive that involved
one brigade in attempt to regain control of the positions it had
lost, but they were repulsed by Ethiopian troops, the office said.
 
</P>
</TEXT>
