that took place in the sea off Besikduzu County, Trabzon Province.
</P>
<P>
Two rowboats carrying dozens of holiday-makers, mostly women and
children, set sail on a cruise to mark a locally celebrated sea
festivity. When a strong northeasterly wind suddenly rose and the
sea became choppy, the boats appeared to keel, capsize and then
sink in high waves.
</P>
