<HEADLINE> Romanian Exports Might Amount to 10 Billion Dollars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, May 22 (Xinhua) -- The main objective of the
Romanian government in 2000 is economic growth to be achieved
mainly through the increase of exports, the amount of which might
reach 10 billion U.S. dollars this year, the official Rompres news
agency Monday quoted government counselor Adrian Vasilescu as
saying.
</P>
<P>
Adrian Vasilescu made the remark late last week at the seminar
on "The truth about Romanian exports."
</P>
<P>
To encourage this sector, the tax on export profit decreased to
five percent, which proved to have a good influence. This measure
led to an increase in exports volume by eight percent, in profits
from exports by 27 percent (2.399 billion U.S. dollars) and an
improvement in exports' structure this year compared with the same
period last year. The tax on export profit would remain five
percent in the next years, Vasilescu stressed.
</P>
<P>
By the end of the year, exports will reach 10 billion dollars.
In the structure of exports, first ranked is the fabrics and ready-
mades industry (610 million U.S. dollars representing 25.5 percent
of the exports' total value. Next ranked are the metallurgical
industry (395 million U.S. dollars representing 16.4 percent) as
well as the wood processing and furniture industry (248 million U.
S. dollars representing 10.4 percent).
</P>
<P>
Exports to developed countries went up by 22.5 percent while
sales to countries in transition increased by 58.7 percent. As
much as 64.8 percent of Romania's trade partners are from the
European Union and 13.5 percent are from central and eastern
Europe, official statistics showed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
