<HEADLINE> Greece's Internet Users Increase Sharply </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
ATHENS, May 22 (Xinhua) -- The number of Internet users in
Greece has increased by 40 percent to some 500,000 this year,
compared to 320,000 at the end of 1999.
</P>
<P>
The increase in the number of Internet users in Greece exceeds
the European average, which is estimated at 70 percent this year,
as the increase rate in Greece is almost certain that will be over
100 percent, according to a research conducted by the Otenet,
which controls 45 percent of the Greek Internet market.
</P>
<P>
An impressive increase was reported in the number of
subscribers to the companies that provide access to the Internet
estimated at 200,000.
</P>
<P>
In Greece, about 15 percent of the population uses a computer
while a third of them surfs on the Internet.
</P>
<P>
It is estimated that by next year the Internet users will be
about 650,000, while it is possible that they could be over 700,
000. 
</P>
</TEXT>
