<HEADLINE> Annan Calls for Increase of U.N. Personnel in Sierra Leone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
He will explain his proposal to the Security Council after a
thorough assessment of the political and military situation in
Sierra Leone, Annan said in his latest report on the U.N. Mission
in Sierra Leone (UNAMSIL), which was released Monday.
</P>
<P>
The Security Council was considering to increase the UNAMSIL's
strength to 13,000 in anticipation of arrival of reinforcements
that would push the force strength beyond the planned 11,100.
</P>
<P>
The UNAMSIL is mandated to monitor the implementation of a
peace accord signed last July by the Sierra Leonean Government and
Foday Sankoh, leader of the rebel Revolutionary United Front (RUF),
with an aim at ending the nation's 9-year civil war.
</P>
<P>
The U.N. will not abandon Sierra Leone whose "plight has become
a crucial test of the solidarity of the international community,"
the U.N. chief noted. 
</P>
