<HEADLINE> U.N. Opens Forum on Role in New Century </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Addressing the U.N. Millennium Forum, Annan said the NGOs (non-
governmental organizations) can "encourage governments to make
their right choices on behalf of the world's poor."
</P>
<P>
The civil society can work at the international level to lift
billions out of poverty by helping them participate in the global
economy, he believed.
</P>
<P>
The NGOs can also help in urging developed nations to open
their markets to poor countries' products and alleviate the latter
's debt burden, he added.
</P>
<P>
Scheduled for May 22-26 as part of the preparations for the U.N.
Millennium Assembly in September, the forum is themed "the United
Nations for the 21st century."
</P>
<P>
The forum's topics include peace, security and disarmament;
eradication of poverty, including debt cancellation and social
development; human rights; sustainable development and the
environment; and the challenges of globalization and strengthening
the Untied Nations and international organizations. 
</P>
