of their tanks destroyed, when they launched an attack to seize an
Eritrean position in Burie, 70 kilometers southwest of Assab, a
port in east Eritrea.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopia launched another failed attack on an Eritrean position
at Omhajer, in the west of the country. Some 450 Ethiopian
soldiers were either killed or wounded, while 11 captured, the
document added.
</P>
<P>
The current round of clashes between the two Horn of Africa
countries renewed on May 12 this year, as a continuation of the
prolonged border conflict first ignited two years ago. Both sides
have claimed inflicting heavy losses on the other side, according
to reports. 
