<HEADLINE> Indian President to Visit China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, May 22 (Xinhua) -- Indian President K. R. Narayanan
will pay a six-day state visit to China starting from May 28, an
Indian External Affairs Ministry statement said here Monday.
</P>
<P>
During his visit, Narayanan will hold wide-ranging talks with
Chinese President Jiang Zemin and other Chinese leaders in his two-
day stay in Beijing and will also visit two other Chinese cities,
Dalian, a port city in northeast China's Liaoning Province, and
Kunming, capital of southwest China's Yunnan Province, the
statement said.
</P>
<P>
The president is also expected to present a bust of world-
famous Indian poet Rabindranath Tagore to China's prestigious
Beijing University, where he will address a gathering of scholars,
academicians, students and officials, the statement added.
</P>
<P>
The president will be accompanied by First Lady Usha Narayanan,
Minister of Heavy Industries and Public Enterprises Manohar Joshi
and four members of the parliament, it noted.
</P>
<P>
Chinese President Jiang visited India in late 1996 while former
Indian President R. Venkataraman went to China in May 1992.
</P>
<P>
China and India marked the 50th anniversary of the
establishment of their diplomatic ties on April 1 this year.
</P>
<P>
According to the Press Trust of India, Indian Prime Minister
Atal Bihari Vajpayee also had a "routine" meeting with President
Narayanan at Rasthrapati Bhavan, or the Presidential Palace, on
Monday evening, during which the two leaders discussed the
president's upcoming visit to China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
