<HEADLINE> China to Map Out Eco-Protection Plan for Western Areas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 22 (Xinhua) -- China will send a delegation of
ecologists to the country's vast western areas to scout out
ecological protection problems that await the massive development
project in the region.
</P>
<P>
According to the project's organizing committee, 13 experts in
ecology, environment and forestry studies from the Chinese Academy
of Sciences, the Chinese Academy of Engineering and other
institutions as well as 22 journalists will set off on June 17.
They are expected to cover 50 counties in 18 provinces.
</P>
<P>
A seminar will be held after the research tour to highlight
strategies for ecological development in the western area, said
chairman of the organizing committee Zhao Nanqi.
</P>
<P>
He pointed that ecological development is as important as
economic development in western areas.  
</P>
