<HEADLINE> German Business Eyes China's Market for Environment-Safe Products </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DALIAN, May 22 (Xinhua) -- The market potential for
environmental protection in China has encouraged a German-funded
firm in northeast China to start processing purified water and
daily drinking water.
</P>
<P>
Prominent Fluid Controls (China) Co., Ltd. produces pumps,
transducers, and ozone generators. It has developed technology for
processing drinking water, waste water, industrial water and water
for special purposes in Dalian, a coastal city in Liaoning
Province. It has undertaken dozens of water processing projects in
China.
</P>
<P>
The company, established in 1994 with 2.15 million U.S. dollars,
invested in China again with another 3.06 million U.S. dollars for
environmentally-friendly products.
</P>
<P>
Viktor Dulger, president of Prominent Fluid Controls Co. (Group)
, said he has noticed that both the Chinese government and its
people are becoming more conscious of the environmental protection
issue. 
