<HEADLINE> Border City First Reports Growth in Trade with DPRK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, May 22 (Xinhua) -- Dandong, a border city in
northeast China's Liaoning Province, has seen its foreign trade
turnover with Democratic People's Republic of Korea surge from 17.
12 percent on a yearly basis to 39.33 million US dollars during
the first quarter of the year.
</P>
<P>
This is the first growth achieved in Sino-DPRK trade in the
past few years, local trade officials said.
</P>
<P>
The main reason for the growth rate may be attributed to the
recovering Korean economy, economists said.
</P>
<P>
With its economy taking a turn for the better, DPRK has started
importing more heavy industrial products such as steel and
machinery other than the traditional import of grain. 
