<HEADLINE> Today's Diplomatic News Highlights (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 22 (Xinhua) -- Following are the highlights of the
diplomatic news released today by Xinhua:
</P>
<P>
 Indian President to Visit China in Late May
</P>
<P>
Indian President Kocheril Raman Narayanan will pay a state
visit to China from May 28 to June 3, at the invitation of Chinese
President Jiang Zemin.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Foreign Ministry spokeswoman Zhang Qiyue announced this
here today.
</P>
<P>
During the visit, the first ever to China since Narayanan
assumed the presidency in 1997, leaders of the two countries will
exchange views on China-India relations and regional and
international issues of mutual interest, Zhang said.
</P>
<P>
 Shanghai Party Secretary Leaves for Four Asian Countries
</P>
<P>
Huang Ju, member of the Political Bureau of the Central
Committee of the Communist Party of China (CPC) and Secretary of
CPC Shanghai Municipal Committee, left here Monday afternoon for a
visit to four Asian countries.
</P>
<P>
The four countries are Vietnam, the Lao's, Japan and the
Republic of Korea.
</P>
<P>
 Sino-U.S. Statement on Cooperation in Environment,
Development Signed
</P>
<P>
China and the United States has signed a joint statement on the
environment and development cooperation between the two countries,
the Chinese Ministry of Science and Technology said today.
</P>
<P>
The statement, signed on May 19 by Chinese Science and
Technology Minister Zhu Lilan and U.S. Ambassador to China Joseph
Prueher on behalf of their respective governments, was released by
the Ministry today.
</P>
<P>
The joint statement said the two countries believe that energy
and environment constitutes one of the most important areas of
cooperation between them.
</P>
<P>
"By making clean energy widely available through the
development and application of new technologies and strengthening
efforts to protect our environment and the earth's biodiversity,
China-U.S. cooperation will contribute significantly toward
further securing the welfare and quality of life of the people of
the two countries," said the statement.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Trade Minister Meets Australian Counterpart
</P>
<P>
Shi Guangsheng, Chinese minister of foreign trade and economic
cooperation, said today that China has entered the final
procedural phase in its bid into the World Trade Organization (WTO)
, and will strictly observe the rules and regulations of the
organization and carry out its commitments.
</P>
<P>
Shi said that relevant laws and regulations are being examined,
supplemented and modified, and management personnel in the
government departments and big enterprises are being trained.
</P>
<P>
Vaile said that his visit has provided a good opportunity for
exchanges between the business communities of the two countries. (
more)
</P>
