<HEADLINE> Embroiderer Donates to Tibet's Potala Palace </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA May 22 (Xinhua) -- China's famous artisan Wang Jingbo
today donated a work of embroidery to the Potala Palace here to
mark the 49th anniversary of the peaceful liberation of Tibet.
</P>
<P>
Wang's embroidered version of the Potala Palace measures 5.8
meters in length and is 3.2 meters wide. It is made with more than
900 colored silk threads and took Wang and his colleagues six
months to complete.
</P>
<P>
A former soldier stationed in Tibet, Wang now lives in east
China's Shandong province and has deep feelings for the Tibetan
people.
</P>
<P>
His embroidered piece of the Potala Palace and another work
featuring the 10th Panchan Lama are valued by experts at two
million yuan (about 240,000 U.S. dollars). 
</P>
