<HEADLINE> Beijing Mayor Meets Photographers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 22 (Xinhua) -- Some 22 photographers from China
and 50 from other countries said "cheese" with Beijing mayor Liu
Qi here today.
</P>
<P>
The photographers are here as part of the "Focus on Beijing"
photo contest, a week-long event organized by the Beijing
Municipal People's Government to present images of the Chinese
capital to the outside world.
</P>
<P>
The mayor thanked them for capturing the history, scenery and
people of Beijing with their unique perspectives and outstanding
skill.
</P>
<P>
He said that the 3,000-year-old city is now experiencing
earthshaking changes while trying to preserve its history. He
hoped that the photographers' works will help the world know more
about Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Liu also said that Beijing will budget about 100 million yuan (
about 12 million U.S. dollars) to help repair and protect the city
's more than 200 historic sites.
</P>
<P>
The contest, which ran from May 16 to 23, attracted
photographers from 24 countries, including the United States,
Canada, Russia and Britain. They went to historical landmarks,
main streets, schools, residential quarters, museums and factories
to capture the essence of Beijing on film.  
</P>
