<HEADLINE> Hutchison Launches Wireless Internet Service </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, May 22 (Xinhua) -- Hutchison Telecom Monday launched
Orangeworld, a wireless Internet service here in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
With the cooperation of 85 content providers, the service
provides dual-band GSM (Global System for Mobile Communications)
and CDMA (Code-Division Multiple-Access) users in Hong Kong with
news and information on entertainment, investment and finance,
travelling, education, technology and shopping.
</P>
<P>
Hutchison Telecom also unified the brand names of all of its
wireless services -- Orange Dual Band, Xin Gan Xian CDMA, Everyday
PCS and paging services into the Orange brand.
</P>
<P>
Hutchison Telecom, formed in 1996 as a subsidiary of Hutchison
Whampoa Group, is the leading telecommunications operator in Hong
Kong with a mobile subscriber base of more than 1.4 million,
representing the largest share of Hong Kong market.  
