<HEADLINE> Meeting on SMEs' Challenges, Opportunities Held in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, May 22 (Xinhua) -- More than 70 certified public
accountants from all over the world gathered here Monday at the
annual meeting of the Independent Accountant International (IA
International) to learn about the challenges and opportunities
faced by Hong Kong's small and medium enterprises (SMEs) during
the economic recovery.
</P>
<P>
Delivering a speech at the meeting, Christopher Cheng, vice
chairman of the Hong Kong General Chamber of Commerce, said Hong
Kong is experiencing a transitional period while recovering from
the Asian financial turmoil. The rapid development of the Internet
and Internet-related business in Hong Kong, together with the
consolidation of the fundamental industries such as trading and
financial services, have accelerated the pace of recovery in the
special administrative region (SAR).
</P>
<P>
Cheng noted that the transformation of the local economy has
brought along challenges and demand for adjustment to both
entrepreneurs and employees. He urged the SAR government to play a
more proactive role in supporting the development of local
industry, the technological sector in particular.
</P>
<P>
As one of the 25 largest international accounting affiliations
in the world, IA International is formed by a network of more than
134 independent accounting firms located in 80 countries. Founded
in 1978, the IA International has its headquarters in Miami,
Florida of the United States.  
</P>
