<HEADLINE> Bombs Rock Island in South Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, May 22 (Xinhua) -- Ten home-made bombs exploded
simultaneously in the southern Philippine island of Mindanao
Sunday night,a report reaching here said Monday.
</P>
<P>
The bombings took place in the coastal towns of Buug and
Malangas in South Zamboanga Province,Philippine News Agency (PNA)
said.
</P>
<P>
But according to the PNA, no one was injured in the blasts and
no suspect was arrested. The damage caused by the explosions is
under estimation.
</P>
<P>
The series of explosions occurred less than three hours after
terrorists set off a powerful bomb at SM Megamall here in Manila,
which killed one person and wounded 17 others.
</P>
<P>
The bomb exploded inside the SM (Shoemart) Megamall, the
biggest shopping mall in the Philippine capital, Sunday afternoon,
the second bombing incident in Manila in less than a week.
</P>
<P>
Last Wednesday, an explosion inside Glorietta mall injured 13
people.
</P>
<P>
On Monday, Philippine President Joseph Estrada condemned the
bombing incidents and vowed to ferret out the terrorists behind
the explosions.
</P>
<P>
These bombings, the president said, were acts of cowardice
committed by terrorists whose agenda is to sow fear among the
people and destabilize the government.
</P>
<P>
He noted the government is not helpless in fighting terrorism."
Let me be clear. We are not helpless in this fight. We can and
will insure the safety and security of all Filipinos throughout
the country," he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
