<HEADLINE> Share Prices Plunge to Year's Low in Singapore </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, May 22 (Xinhua) -- Share prices plunged to this year
's low on Singapore Stock Market Monday as U.S. NASDAQ's 4-percent
drop on Friday and U.S. Federal Reserve's tough stance on
inflation dampened market sentiment.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark Straits Times Index (STI) dropped 62.54 points to
end at 1,929.88 in light trading.
</P>
<P>
The market volume totaled 234 million shares worth 524.96
million Singapore dollars (303.92 million U.S. dollars). Declining
issues overwhelmed advancers by 284 to 54 with 203 counters
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
The larger block was a 12.52 million parcel by SingTel which
was transacted at 2.23 Singapore dollars per share. It was
followed by NatElec which had 11.21 million units done. Chew
EuHock was the next with 10.39 million counters changing hands.
</P>
<P>
Bukit Sem led the ascent of the day climbing up 40 cents to
close at 13.4 Singapore dollars. SembLog edged up 30 cents to
finish at 10.4 Singapore dollars. Datacrft inched up 15 cents to
end at 7.75 U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Creative 50 was the biggest loser of the day, plummeting 300
cents to close at 44.1 Singapore dollars. SPH sank 160 cents to
finish at 27.6 Singapore dollars. SPH tumbled by 150 cents to end
at 27.6 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
Dealers attributed Monday's sharp drop in share prices to the
bearish sentiment following NASDAQ's big losses on Friday and U.S.
Federal Reserve's signal that it would not go soft on curbing
inflation.
</P>
<P>
They also noted that electronic stocks suffered the heaviest
losses and banking stocks also fared poorly. 
</P>
</TEXT>
