<HEADLINE> Rise Plan in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, May 22 (Xinhua) -- An international symposium on the
implementation of the Rise Plan in China was held here today in
Jiangmen, in the south China province of Guangdong.
</P>
<P>
The Rise Plan, standing for the Regional Integration for
Sustainable Economies, is a project launched by the Asia Pacific
Economic Cooperation (APEC) and the Pacific Economic Cooperation
Council (PECC) last year. The project is aimed at promoting
sustainable economic development in rural areas.
</P>
<P>
Jiangmen, a central city in the west Pearl River Delta, was
approved as the site for the Rise plan last October.
</P>
<P>
PECC hopes to create a model for pushing forward the economic
development in rural areas in Asia by carrying out the plan in
Jiangmen, said Carole Brookings, chairperson of the executive
committee of the Rise Plan.  
</P>
