<HEADLINE> China to Award "Child Scientists" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 22 (Xinhua) -- Middle school students in China
with excellent scientific grades will have the chance to receive
the "Cheung Kong Child Scientist Award".
</P>
<P>
Wei Yu, Vice Minister of Education said at a press conference
today that the award aims to encourage more outstanding middle
school students in China to take part in scientific innovation
activities.
</P>
<P>
"Cheung Kong Child Scientist Award" is a special program
jointly sponsored by the Ministry of Education and Hong Kong
entrepreneur Li Ka-shing and his Cheung Kong Infrastructure
Holdings Limited.
</P>
<P>
According to the program, students from middle schools, normal
schools and vocational high schools will have the chance to
receive awards worth a total of five million yuan (602,400 U.S.
dollars).
</P>
<P>
The China Association for Science and Technology will invite 20
famous scholars and scientists to form an appraisement committee.
