<HEADLINE> One Person Dead in Helicopter Crash </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, May 22 (Xinhua) -- At least one person was killed
this evening when a helicopter exploded in mid-air over Changsha,
the capital city of central China's Hunan province.
</P>
<P>
Witnesses said that around 6:10 p.m., a red helicopter was
flying low over Juzizhoutou Park in the city, when it suddenly
exploded and plunged into the Xiangjiang River.
</P>
<P>
People in the vicinity of the crash hurried to the scene, and
rescued five people out of the river.
</P>
<P>
So far, one person has been confirmed dead, and the other four
were taken to the hospital. Two of them are in serious condition,
doctors said.
</P>
<P>
The helicopter belonged to the Hunan Yuanda Air Conditioning
Company, a famous private business of the country.
</P>
<P>
It is one of the two helicopters that Yuanda purchased from
abroad in 1997. The purchase caused a sensation throughout the
country at the time.
</P>
<P>
At press time, investigators were working to determine the
cause of the incident.  
</P>
