<HEADLINE> Iran Reiterates Support for Lebanese Resistance Against Israel </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, May 22 (Xinhua) -- Foreign Ministry spokesman Hamid Reza
Asefi Monday reiterated Iran's support for Lebanon's resistance
movement against Israel, the Islamic Republic News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
On the planned withdrawal of Israeli forces from south Lebanon,
Asefi said that it was a victory of the resistance movement of
Hezbollah guerrillas and other popular forces who have enjoyed
long-time Iranian backing.
</P>
<P>
Iran believes that Israel should withdraw from the territories
in south Lebanon unconditionally so that security and calm would be
restored in the country, he said.
</P>
<P>
He called on Arab and Muslim countries in the Middle East to
continue pressuring Israel to join the Nuclear Non-Proliferation
Treaty and put its nuclear arms under international supervision.
</P>
<P>
He expressed hope that through further coordination among the
regional countries in the future, the goal of a nuclear-free Middle
East would be realized soon.
</P>
<P>
Israel has set July 7 as the deadline for its withdrawal of
forces from south Lebanon, where it has kept a so-called buffer
zone with a self-claimed aim of protecting its north from cross-
border guerrilla attacks.
</P>
<P>
Iran has refused to recognize the Israeli regime since the 1979
Islamic revolution and it has always called for armed struggle
against the Jewish state for the return of Arab and Islamic lands.
</P>
