<HEADLINE> EU Foreign Ministers Welcome EU-China WTO Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, May 22 (Xinhua) -- Foreign ministers of the European
Union (EU) on Monday welcomed the bilateral agreement between the
EU and China on the latter's entry into the World Trade
Organization (WTO).
</P>
<P>
The foreign ministers, meeting at their general affairs council,
heard and welcomed a report from EU chief negotiator Pascal Lamy
on the latest round of talks on China's WTO accession.
</P>
<P>
"The agreement appeared to be a sound commercial package and to
have taken full account of the EU's specific trade interests, as
required in the mandate given to the European Commission by the
council on April 10," said the foreign ministers in a written
statement.
</P>
<P>
"The council felt that the completion of the EU's bilateral
negotiations with China represented a major step toward China's
ultimate accession to the WTO," added the statement.
</P>
<P>
The completion of the EU-China WTO talks preceded a vote
scheduled for this week by the U.S. Congress on the provision of
permanent normal trade relations (PNTR) for China. 
</P>
