<DOCNO> XIE20000522.0123 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-05-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mobile Phone Users Tops 8 Million In Guangdong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, May 22 (Xinhua) -- Mobile phone subscribers in south
China's Guangdong Province today topped eight million, an average
of nine mobile phones for every 100 residents.
</P>
<P>
The number of phone subscribers in Guangdong accounts for one-
sixth of the country's total, ranking first among Chinese
provinces, autonomous regions and municipalities.
</P>
<P>
The wireless telecommunication network in Guangdong has
witnessed enormous growth since the province opened the country's
first mobile phone line in 1987, said a local economic official.
</P>
<P>
Five years ago, the province only had one million mobile phone
users, said the official. By the end of last year, Guangdong
reported an increase to six million mobile phone users.
</P>
<P>
The province is making efforts to upgrade network technology.
Local mobile phone exchanges will have a handling capacity of
nearly 20 million lines after upgrading is completed by the end of
this year.
</P>
<P>
By that time, there will be 10 million mobile phone users in
China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
