<HEADLINE> China Issues Treasury Bonds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 22 (Xinhua) -- China will issue 14 billion yuan
worth of treasury bonds to private investors on Tuesday, the
Ministry of Finance announced here today.
</P>
<P>
This is the fourth batch of T-bonds that China issued for
private investors so far this year. The 10-year bond has a
floating interest rate pegged on the interest rate of one-year
bank savings, and the fixed interest rate difference is 0.62
percent.
