<BODY>
<HEADLINE> More Chinese Become Overweight, Obesity: Research </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 22 (Xinhua) -- "Keep your weight at a safe level!"
More and more Chinese get this advice, or the health warning, from
doctors as obesity is becoming a major epidemic in this populous
country.
</P>
<P>
It is estimated that 18 out of every 100 people in China are
overweight. The rate of obesity has reached 2.48 percent, which
means at least 30 million people older than 20 are overweight.
</P>
<P>
Overweight among people aged between 35-59 has even surpassed
50 percent, the average level in some industrialized countries,
according to the latest research.
</P>
<P>
Residents in north China, especially males in Beijing and
females in Shandong Province, run higher risk of having extra
weight than those in the south. Females and urban residents are
more likely to become fat than males and rural people.
</P>
<P>
"Obesity is not only a health-threatening illness, but also the
key risk factor of some other diseases, such as diabetes, cardio
and cerebral vascular illnesses, and respiratory system problems,"
according to researchers from the Chinese Academy of Preventive
Medicine, the Chinese Academy of Medical Science and the No. 1
Hospital of Beijing University.
</P>
<P>
The researchers employed the BMI index -- body weight (
kilometer)/square of body height (meter), which has been
recommended by the World Health Organization.
</P>
<P>
A person can be diagnosed overweight if the BMI equals or
surpasses 25, while the criteria of obesity is 30 or higher.
</P>
<P>
However, some Asian scholars argue that bottom lines for
overweight and obesity diagnosis among Asians should be
respectively lowered to 23 and 25, because the Asians are more
vulnerable to diabetes and cardio vascular diseases.
</P>
<P>
If this is the case, China will have a larger population of
overweight people. The researchers said specific measures should
be drawn up as soon as possible to deal with the problem. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000522.0129 </DOCNO>
