</P>
<P>
According to the official news agency Angop, the delegations
from Angola, Brazil, Guinea-Bissau, Mozambique, Portugal and Sao
Tome and Principe attended the two-day meeting.
</P>
<P>
After the conference, the visiting delegations are expected to
meet with the Angolan president Jose Eduardo dos Santos.
</P>
<P>
At their last meeting held in the Cape Verdean capital the
Praia City, the CPLP defense ministers debated a document on the
globalization of the technical and military cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Angola, which has been suffering the civil conflicts for some
26 years, has gained advantage in the battlefields since late
1999, and is currently soliciting international support for the
annihilation of the rebels led by Jonas Savimbi.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the South African army chief of staff General S.
Nyanda is also scheduled to start his 4-day visit to Angola on
Monday, at the invitation of his Angolan counterpart Joao Baptista
de Matos.
</P>
<P>
Nyanda will meet the commander-in-chief of the Angolan Armed
Forces (FAA) Jose Eduardo dos Santos, and defense minister Kundi
Paihama. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
