<DOCNO> XIE20000522.0154 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-05-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indonesia's Budget May Need to be Revised, Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, May 22 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia's Coordinating Minister
for Economy, Finance and Industry Kwik Kian Gie said here Monday
that the state budget for fiscal year 2000 needs to be revised if
the exchange rate of rupiah stands at 8,000 per U.S. dollar.
</P>
<P>
"If the rupiah continues to weaken and standing at 8,000 per
dollar,the (current) state budget needs to be revised," Kwik told
reporters.
</P>
<P>
The government had set the exchange rate of rupiah within the
current fiscal year ending in December at 7,000 rupiah for one U.S.
dollar.
</P>
<P>
But the rupiah dropped to a six months low against the
greenback last week, hitting around 8,500 per U.S. dollar last
week. But it was quoted at 8,100 (buying) and 8,350 (selling) per
dollar Monday morning.
</P>
<P>
Last week, Minister of Finance Bambang Sudibyo said the
government would not revise its current budget as the exchange
rate of rupiah is still susceptible.
</P>
<P>
While Kwik backed Sudibyo's statement hoping that in the future
the rupiah will regain strength, he added "we can not predict when
the rupiah will strengthen as we hope."  
</P>
</TEXT>
