<HEADLINE> Klim May Drop Olympic 200 Meters Freestyle </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, May 22 (Xinhua) -- Australian swimmer Michael Klim,
the world champion in the 200 meters freestyle, may drop the event
in his Sydney Olympics schedule to concentrate on winning gold in
five other events.
</P>
<P>
Klim, 21, finished second to world record holder Ian Thorpe at
the Australian selection trials in Sydney last week and would have
a tough task beating the 17-year-old teammate who broke three
world records last week.
</P>
<P>
"Swimming three 200m races because of the semifinal format is
very demanding and it could jeopardize my chances in the 100m
butterfly and 100m freestyle," Klim said.
</P>
<P>
Klim has also earned a berth in the 100m butterfly and 100m
freestyle and is likely to swim both freestyle relays and the
4x100m medley relay. 
</P>
