<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Anti-Narcotics Education for Over 60 Million School Children in 1999 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 22 (Xinhua) -- More than 60 million Chinese
primary and secondary students received anti-narcotics education
in 1999, the Ministry of Public Security said today.
</P>
<P>
Of these 60 million students, more than 26 million are
secondary school students and 35 million are primary school
students.
</P>
<P>
China's schools usually conduct anti-narcotics education in the
form of holding lectures, exhibitions, and composition contests or
organizing students to read anti-narcotics books or watch related
films or VCDs.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that China had over 680,000 registered drug
addicts in 1999, 14.3 percent more than in 1998.
</P>
<P>
Among the total drug population, 80 percent of the registered
addicts are male, and people between the ages of 17 and 35 take up
78 percent. More than 490,000, or 72 percent of the total, take
heroin. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
