<HEADLINE> Four Persons Killed in Fire in Manila </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, May 22 (Xinhua) -- Four persons were killed when fire
struck a two-storey residential house in Quezon city, Metro Manila
Monday, local police said.
</P>
<P>
Arson investigator Fortunato Alde of the Quezon City Fire
Station said initial probe showed that the fire broke out at the
two-storey duplex-type residential house early Monday morning.
</P>
<P>
Alde said the bodies of all victims were found after the fire
were put out. But he added that two others in the house have
survived the fire.
</P>
<P>
Damage to property and the cause of the fire are still being
determined, Alde said. 
</P>
