<DATE_TIME> 2000-05-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Share Prices Plunge in Tokyo, Nikkei Hits Year's New Closing Low </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Nikkei Stock Average of 225 selected issues on the First
Section of the Tokyo Stock Exchange declined 472.16 points, or 2.
80 percent from last Friday's close to end at 16,386.01, renewing
this year's lowest closing for the second straight trading day.
</P>
<P>
The broader-based Tokyo Stock Price Index (TOPIX), covering all
First Section issues, also hit the lowest closing for the year,
losing 55.88 points or 3.54 percent to 1,522.49.
</P>
<P>
Turnover on the major section decreased to 609.63 million
shares from last Friday's 670.24 million shares.
</P>
<P>
Nippon Steel was the day's volume leader.
</P>
<P>
Information and technology issues faced selling following a
plunge in New York's technology-heavy Nasdaq composite index last
Friday.
</P>
<P>
Reflecting the sluggishness in share prices, brokerages were
the biggest losers, falling 7.58 percent as a group, while
wholesalers, consumer finance firms and banks also saw large
declines.
</P>
<P>
Low- and medium-priced issues drew buying, traders said, adding
that construction firms, real estate firms and nonlife insurers
were also up.
</P>
<P>
Of the issues listed on the First Section, losers far
outnumbered gainers 977 to 279, with 132 issues closing unchanged.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
