<HEADLINE> Thai-Branded Products to be Promoted in ASEAN </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, May 22 (Xinhua) -- The Thai government is supporting a
move to promote Thai-branded products in the Association of
Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN) market by allowing local
advertising agencies to take part in the campaign, the Thai News
Agency (TNA) reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
Deputy Director-General of the Department of Export Promotion
Charin Harnsuebsai was quoted as saying that the move would
benefit both exporters of Thai-branded products and local
advertising agencies, which have said they are ready to join
manufacturers and exporters in promoting Thai brands in other nine
ASEAN countries.
</P>
<P>
ASEAN now groups Brunei, Cambodia, Indonesia, Laos, Malaysia,
Myanmar, the Philippines, Singapore, Thailand and Vietnam.
</P>
<P>
The move coincides with the preparations by ASEAN states to
implement the ASEAN Free Trade Area (AFTA) over the next three
years.
</P>
<P>
Thai manufacturers and exporters who have already created their
own brands and those who are going to introduce their own ones can
now turn to local advertising agencies to help promote and
publicize their Thai-branded products in the ASEAN market, said
the report. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
