<HEADLINE> MILF Intends to Resume Talks With Philippine Govt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, May 22 (Xinhua) -- The Moro Islamic Liberation Front (
MILF)expressed its intent to resume peace talks with the
Philippine government later this month, the Philippine News Agency
said Monday.
</P>
<P>
Aleem Abdulaziz Mimbantas, MILF chief peace negotiator, was
quoted as saying that their intention came amid the government's
pronouncement of maintaining an open line to peace options with
them despite recent clashes of their forces in flashpoint areas of
Mindanao.
</P>
<P>
The MILF's move came after it indefinitely suspended its almost
three-year-old talks with the government earlier this month due to
continuous clashes of their respective combatants in the field.
</P>
<P>
On Sunday, government chief negotiator Edgardo Batenga
reiterated the government's position to entertain peace ventures
with the MILF to forge lasting peace in the island.
</P>
<P>
As sign of their sincerity to the proposal, Al Haj Murad, MILF
military chief, has announced the repositioning of their forces
back to Camp Abubakar, their biggest camp located in the jungle of
Maguindana, within 48 hours starting today to clear the Ramos
highway of resisting guerrillas. 
</P>
</TEXT>
