<HEADLINE> World Bank to Help Thailand Develop IT Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, May 22 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank (WB) will cooperate
with the Thai government to develop information technology (IT) in
Thailand, which will lead to new approaches of economic
development in the country, Thailand's Science, Technology and
Environment Minister Arthit Urairat said here Monday.
</P>
<P>
Arthit was quoted by the official Thai News Agency as saying
that he had discussed the issue with executives of the World Bank
recently, and the WB officials are scheduled to fly to Thailand
this week to work out the cooperative project with the Ministry of
Science, Technology, and Environment.
</P>
<P>
The cooperation would help enhance the competitiveness of both
the public and private sectors in the local IT industry, which
would lead to the economic development, based on new IT-oriented
approaches, he noted.
</P>
<P>
Information technology is now seen as a key element of modern
economic development policies of countries in the globalization
era, said Arthit, and with the help by the World Bank, Thailand's
competitiveness in the international market will be enhanced.
</P>
