<HEADLINE> Transportation Emphasized in Guangdong's 10th Five-Year Plan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, May 22 (Xinhua) -- Officials in south China's
Guangdong Province said that building transportation networks will
be an important task in the 10th five-year plan of the 2001-2005
period.
</P>
<P>
According to the officials, the fast-growing coastal province
will invest heavily to build an expressway network that will
connect prefecture-level cities throughout the province.
</P>
<P>
Guangdong will also construct a light rail that will link up
main cities in the Pearl River Delta, Hong Kong and Macao, while
continuing to build subways in Guangzhou and Shenzhen cities.
</P>
<P>
In the meantime, the province will build more airports and the
New Guangzhou International Airport. The construction of inland
river navigation routes will also be expanded.
</P>
<P>
These construction projects, including the installation of
special pipelines to transport drinking water, will help improve
the quality of living standards in the Pearl River Delta. 
</P>
