<BODY>
<HEADLINE> ACFTU Openly Selects Cadres </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 22 (Xinhua) -- Ninety-eight cadres from China's
provincial trade unions have been competing for 11 departmental
deputy head positions within the All-China Federation of Trade
Unions (ACFTU) in the last two days.
</P>
<P>
An ACFTU official noted that it is the first time for ACFTU to
openly select cadres. The ACFTU was asked to follow the principle
of "openness, fairness and selection of the best candidate through
competition," according to today's "Worker's Daily".
</P>
<P>
From April 1, ACFTU began to prepare for this cadre selecting
work. The final round of cadre assessments is still being
processed.
</P>
<P>
The ACFTU official said that openly selecting cadres aims to
provide a channel for capable and talented cadres and promote
competition among them. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
