<DOCNO> XIE20000522.0228 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-05-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cooperation Award Granted to Japanese Agronomist </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 22 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese government today
conferred the 1999 International Scientific and Technological
Cooperation Award to the late Japanese agronomist, Shouyichi
Yishimoto.
</P>
<P>
His wife received the state award on behalf of her late husband
who passed away in February this year soon after the award was
announced by the Chinese government in January.
</P>
<P>
Zhu Lilan, Minister of Science and Technology, said at the
award ceremony today that Shouyichi Yishimoto had worked in Sino-
Japanese agricultural science exchanges from 1974.
</P>
<P>
He was the first foreign expert to introduce the use of plastic
sheeting to Chinese farmers. In the past 25 years, the Japanese
agronomist visited China for over 100 times providing technical
training and guidance in the application of plastic sheeting and
other farming skills.
</P>
<P>
Zhu Lilan said the Japanese expert also helped implement
several major Sino-Japanese cooperative programs and made
outstanding contributions to China's agricultural growth and
promotion of Sino-Japanese friendship.
</P>
<P>
An official with the Ministry of Agriculture said with the help
of the Japanese expert, China began to apply the use the plastic
sheeting in growing vegetables in 1979 and then to growing other
crops in 30 provinces, municipalities and autonomous regions.
</P>
<P>
Shouyichi Yishimoto, who was born in January, 1925, learnt of
the award news in the hospital.
</P>
<P>
Zhu said China will promote international scientific
cooperation with foreign countries in the new century.
</P>
<P>
Granted by the State Council, the International Scientific and
Technological Cooperation Award is conferred annually to up to
four foreign scientists, engineers, government officials or
organizations for their outstanding achievements for promoting
bilateral or multi-lateral scientific cooperation and development.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
