<HEADLINE> More Handicapped Chinese Go to College </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 22 (Xinhua) -- A total of 1,381 handicapped
students in China were admitted to college last year, accounting
for 90 percent of such examinees who passed the matriculation
examinations last July, the China Disabled Persons' Federation
said today.
</P>
<P>
With the care and help from the Chinese Communist Party and
governments at all levels, more than 6,300 handicapped youth have
been admitted to institutions of higher learning, according to the
federation.
</P>
<P>
These students in universities and colleges have also won
respect from peers for their hard work, fortitude to overcome
difficulties and their academic performance.
</P>
<P>
In addition to these institutions mentioned above that help
train the handicapped, 998 special vocational schools across the
country have provided training for 580,000 physically-
handicapped students over the years.  
</P>
