<HEADLINE> Macao Raises Deposit Interest Rates </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, May 22 (Xinhua) -- Annual deposit rates in Macao were
raised by 0.5 percentage points across the board beginning from
Monday.
</P>
<P>
The decision was made last weekend by the Macao Association of
Banks right after the Hong Kong Association of Banks announced
last Friday to raise deposit rates in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
In this sense, the interest rate for current deposit in Macao
was raised from 4 percent to 4.5 percent per annum, and the rate
for seven-day fix deposit was raised from 4.75 percent to 5.25
percent.
</P>
<P>
People with the banking sector in Macao said that the increase
of deposit rates may hold off the recovery of local economy which
has suffered depression over the past years.  
</P>
