<HEADLINE> More Multi-Media Teaching Centers Opened in Myanmar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, May 22 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar is implementing education
promotion program for all round development of students and uplift
of education to international level by opening more and more multi-
media teaching centers in the country.
</P>
<P>
So far, over 300 such teaching centers have been opened
nationwide under the program, official newspaper The New Light of
Myanmar reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
The government has laid down plans to catch up with developed
nations in Southeast Asia in four years, it said, quoting
Lieutenant-General Khin Nyunt, first secretary of the Myanmar
State Peace and Development Council, who inaugurated a multi-media
teaching center at a basic education junior high school here
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The Myanmar education ministry has widely introduced multi-
media teaching and learning aids in basic education schools in the
country since last year.
</P>
<P>
According to official statistics, basic education schools
totaled 42,894 in Myanmar as of April, of which 37,627 are primary
schools, while 3,695 are junior high and 1,572 senior high schools.
</P>
<P>
At present, altogether 225,403 teachers are teaching more than
700,000 students and every year more than 100,000 students
complete basic education, the statistics show.. 
</P>
