<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY -- Kuwaiti Oil Minister Sheikh Saud Nasser Al-Sabah
said here Sunday that current oil prices in the world market are
fair.
</P>
<P>
On recent oil prices rise despite major oil producers' raising
of their output on April 1, Sheikh Saud said "there is a balance
in the market with regards to supply and demand." (Kuwait-Current
Oil Prices)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
PHNOM PENH -- Cambodia will again have abundant crops in the
new year after a good harvest last year, sacred oxen indicated
Sunday during the annual Royal Plowing Festival held in front of
the National Museum.
</P>
<P>
King Norodom Sihanouk and Queen Norodom Monineath Sihanouk
attended the ceremony. The king was in high spirits, beaming and
waving to his subjects. (Cambodia-Good Harvests)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
DHAKA -- Most of the newly imported double-decker buses of the
Bangladesh Road Transport Corporation (BRTC) remain idle due to
bureaucratic tangle, the New Nation reported Sunday.
</P>
<P>
A fleet of 68 double-decker buses imported from India on state
credit provided by the Indian government reached Dhaka early last
month for the convenience of the city commuters. (Bangladesh-
Imported Buses)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
DHAKA -- Bangladesh had earned about 57 million U.S. dollars by
exporting 1.288 million bales of raw jute till April 15 this year
which registered an increase over that of the previous year, the
New Nation reported Sunday.
</P>
<P>
According to the report, Indian buyers alone imported around
600,000 bales of raw jute, Pakistan 300,000, Thailand 125,000,
Brazil 150,000 and other countries 113,000 during the period. (
Bangladesh-Jute Export)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
NEW DELHI -- India's inflation rate reached a 73-week high of 6.
31 percent for the week ended May 6 mainly due to a sharp increase
in prices of some food articles and petroleum products, an
official release said here Sunday.
</P>
<P>
This has been the highest inflation rate of the country since
December 9, 1998, when a 6.8-percent inflation rate was recorded,
said the release. (India-Inflation)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
DHAKA -- Bangladeshi banks had 4.8 billion U.S. dollars in
default loans at the end of the first six months of the current
fiscal year.
</P>
<P>
The New Nation Sunday quoted sources of Bangladesh Bank as
saying this amount is nearly 43 percent of the total loans
disbursed in the same period. (Bangladesh-Bank Loans) 
