<HEADLINE> NW Province to Invest Heavily in Highway Construction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LANZHOU, May 22 (Xinhua) -- Northwest China's Gansu Province
plans to spend 5 billion yuan (602 million U.S. dollars) on
improving transportation facilities in the next five years, and
increase highway length by 2,200 km.
</P>
<P>
Some 4.29 billion yuan (some 517 million dollars) will be used
to build highways and investment for rural road construction will
total 600 million yuan (some 72.29 million dollars).
</P>
<P>
Construction on eight main roads, including Baiyin-Lanzhou,
Liugouhe-Gulang, Yongchang-Shandan has already started and will be
completed in two years.
</P>
<P>
At present, there are still over 2,500 villages in Gansu that
do not have access to bus transport due to adverse natural
conditions and fund shortage.  
</P>
