<HEADLINE> Indonesian Nabbed for Illegal Communications in Myanmar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, May 22 (Xinhua) -- The Myanmar authorities recently
nabbed an Indonesian for illegally carrying out overseas
communications work by installing a satellite dish and using
sophisticated communications systems.
</P>
<P>
Irawan Sidaria was caught with 15 communication devices
including the United-States-made satellite dish installed and used
at the Asia Plaza Hotel, a private-run hotel in downtown Yangon.
</P>
<P>
Irawan, who arrived in Myanmar in April, hired a room at the
hotel under the pretext of opening a company office to conduct the
activities, the authorities charged.
</P>
<P>
The satellite dish was installed in such a way that it directed
towards a Thai communication satellite named Inmarse over the
Indian Ocean without using the communication link of state-run
Myanma Posts and Telecommunications, the sole agent operating
communication services in Myanmar.
</P>
<P>
A Filipino and an American were also involved in the activities,
the report added.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the authorities also warned that action will be
taken against illegal local and overseas communications by use of
satellite communications equipment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
