<HEADLINE> St Gallen Wins Swiss League Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, May 21 (Xinhua) -- St Gallen Won their first Swiss
league title for 96 years on Sunday when second-placed Basle were
held to a 1-1 draw at Servette.
</P>
<P>
Basle, needing a victory, saw their slender title hopes
disappear when Ermin Siljak scored the equaliser three minutes
from time. St Gallen have 49 points, 10 more than Basle, with
three games remaining.
</P>
<P>
St Gallen, established in 1879, are Switzerland's oldest club.
They forced Christian Gross's team into a must-win situation after
posting a 2-1 victory at Lucerne on Friday.
</P>
<P>
It is only the second time in St Gallen's history they have
lifted the title, their last success coming in 1904.
</P>
<P>
St Gallen will be Switzerland's Champions League
representatives next season. 
</P>
</TEXT>
