Minister Joschka Fischer on building a European federation as a
way to make the future European Union a politically strong entity.
</P>
<P>
"We are in the presence of a tendency in Germany to imaging for
Europe a federal structure which corresponds to its own model. In
depth, it (Germany) always dreams of the Roman-Germanic Holy
Empire," said Chevenement in an interview with France 2 television
channel.
</P>
<P>
The German proposal, made on May 12 by Fischer and tacitly
supported by German Chancellor Gerhard Schroeder, includes a
European federal constitution, a directly elected European
executive government, and a two-chamber parliament based on the
model of the German parliament. (France-Germany-Chevenement)
