<HEADLINE> KFOR Discovers Large Amount of Ammunition in Kosovo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, May 21 (Xinhua) -- The international peacekeeping
force in Kosovo (KFOR) recently discovered a large amount of
ammunition and 100 sets of brand-new U.S. army uniforms in Drenica
to the southwest of Kosovo capital Pristina, the Tanjug news
agency reported Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The military material discovered includes infantry weapons,
landmines, ammunition and complete sets of U.S. army uniforms, it
reported.
</P>
<P>
Drenica was a military base of the former illegal Kosovo
Liberation Army (KLA) with shooting ranges and barracks, Tanjug
said.
</P>
<P>
The new discovery shows the United States is still secretly
arming the Kosovo Protection Corps (KPC), reorganized from the KLA,
in a bid to help ethnic Albanians achieve their independence in
Kosovo, Tanjug said.
</P>
<P>
In doing this, the United States has seriously violated the U.N.
Security Council Resolution 1244, it noted. 
</P>
