the New York Knicks beat the Miami Heat 83-82 to win the Eastern
Conference Semi-finals on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
As they have over the past four post-seasons, New York and
Miami scratched and clawed for the slightest advantage.
</P>
<P>
Four of the seven games went down to the final possession and
the teams were separated by only six points.
</P>
<P>
The Knicks will face the top-seeded Indiana Pacers on Tuesday
in a rematch of last year's conference finals, won by New York in
six games.
</P>
<P>
Patrick Ewing had 20 points and 10 rebounds for the Knicks, who
had a 10-3 run over the last four minutes. Ewing scored the game's

final points on a dunk with 1:20 to go and New York did not take
another shot.
</P>
<P>
Last year, the Heat lost to the Knicks on a miraculous shot by
Allan Houston. This year, they can blame only themselves. They
blew an 18-point lead in Game Six and an 11-point edge Sunday.
</P>
<P>
In the fourth quarter, they missed their first five free throws
and made just one basket in the final 4:45, squandering a 79-73
lead. 
