<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 22 (Xinhua) -- Highlights of today's major Beijing-
based newspapers:
</P>
<P>
People's Daily
</P>
<P>
-- An editorial, titled "Great Guiding Principle for
Strengthening Party Building Comprehensively," calls for
strengthening of the Communist Party of China (CPC) in line with
President Jiang Zemin's recent remarks about Party building.
</P>
<P>
The editorial says that Jiang's comments that the CPC
represents advanced productivity, an advanced culture and the
fundamental interests of the people in China have both immediate
and long-term significance.
</P>
<P>
-- Chinese President Jiang Zemin met on Sunday with senior
Chinese army officers attending a conference on the political work
at the military academies and universities.
</P>
<P>
The conference was designed to carry out Jiang Zemin's series
of important instructions on the building of the military
academies and universities and to explore ways and means of
improving the political work at the academies and universities,
under the guidance of Deng Xiaoping Theory.
</P>
<P>
