<HEADLINE> Two Child Hostages Rescued in Southern Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, May 22 (Xinhua) -- Philippine government troops rescued
two child hostages in Basilan Sunday afternoon in a clash with Abu
Sayyaf rebels, the local ABS-CBN television reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
It said that one soldier and several Abu Sayyaf rebels were
injured in the clash.
</P>
<P>
The two school children were among a group of about 50 people
seized by the Abu Sayyaf rebels from two schools on March 20. Six
were killed and most of the rest were either released or rescued.
</P>
<P>
But seven hostages, two female teachers and five school
children,are still in the hands of the rebel group, it said.
</P>
