<HEADLINE> Cheruiyot and De Reuck Win Road Race Titles  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, May 21 (Xinhua) -- Kenya's Reuben Cheruiyot and
South African Colleen DeReuck captured the men's and women's
titles at the Bay to Breakers 12-kilometer road race in San
Francisco, California on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Cheruiyot completed the race through San Francisco's city
streets and Golden Gate Park, with a finish overlooking the
Pacific Ocean, in 34 minutes 54 seconds. His Compatriot Dominic
Kirui was second in 35:25 and Mexico's Armando Quintanilla came in
third in 35:30.
</P>
<P>
DeReuck clocked 38:42 and was followed home by Russian Lydia
Grigorieva in 39:37 and Kenyan Pauline Konga in 39.48. 
</P>
