<HEADLINE> Nepalese Woman Scales Mt. Qomolangma from North Side  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, May 21 (Xinhua) -- Ms Pemba Sherpa from Nepal
summitted the 8848-meter high Mount Qomolangma from north side
from China at 9:20 a.m. on May 19, according to the message
received from Qomolangma Base Camp Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Ms Pemba Sherpa is a member of the Swiss Qomolangma Expedition
Spring 2000 led by Karl Kohler. She is the third Nepali woman to
scale the highest peak on earth and the first Nepali women to
scale the peak from the north side. 
</P>
