<HEADLINE> Nepali Summiter Scales Mt. Qomolangma in Shortest Time  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, May 21 (Xinhua) -- Babu Chhiri Sherpa set a world
record by reaching atop the 8848-meter high Mount Qomolangma in
the shortest ever time and without using aritficial oxygen.
</P>
<P>
According to the Nepali Ministry of Tourism, the 34-year-old
climber took 15 hours and 56 seconds to reach the summit of the
world's highest peak. He started climbing from the base camp (
5300m) at 5:00 a.m. on May 20. 
</P>
</TEXT>
