<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kovacs Sets European 50 meters Breaststroke Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, May 21 (Xinhua) -- Hungarian swimmer Agnes Kovacs broke
a European women's 50 meters breaststroke record of 31.34 seconds
in the Mare Nostrum swimming meeting in Monaco on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Kovacs eclipsed the previous mark of 31.43 seconds set by
German Zoe Baker during the European championships in Istanbul in
July.
</P>
<P>
The 19-year-old was four hundredths of a second short of the
European 200 meters breaststroke record only 40 minutes earlier,
and one 1/100th shy of the 100 meters record in the same
discipline on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
It was the second European record in the competition in which a
world record has also been broken.
</P>
<P>
Dutch woman Inge de Bruijn broke the women's 50 meters
butterfly world record on Saturday and followed that by breaking
her own European 100 meters record in the same discipline.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000522.0303 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-05-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kovacs Sets European 50 meters Breaststroke Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, May 21 (Xinhua) -- Hungarian swimmer Agnes Kovacs broke
a European women's 50 meters breaststroke record of 31.34 seconds
in the Mare Nostrum swimming meeting in Monaco on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Kovacs eclipsed the previous mark of 31.43 seconds set by
Briton Zoe Baker during the European championships in Istanbul in
July.
</P>
<P>
The 19-year-old was four hundredths of a second short of the
European 200 meters breaststroke record only 40 minutes earlier,
and one 1/100th shy of the 100 meters record in the same
discipline on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
It was the second European record in the competition in which a
world record has also been broken.
</P>
<P>
Dutch woman Inge de Bruijn broke the women's 50 meters
butterfly world record on Saturday and followed that by breaking
her own European 100 meters record in the same discipline.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
