<DOCNO> XIE20000522.0309 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-05-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing Spreads Population Education in Colleges </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 22 (Xinhua) -- Nearly 10,000 college students in
Beijing recently signed their names to a proposal calling on
youngsters to learn more about population growth and its impact on
the environment.
</P>
<P>
This is part of the effort this year to educate the city's
college students about population control.
</P>
<P>
"We are responsible for our future generations, we are
responsible for our tomorrow," the written proposal said. "We
should take a scientific attitude towards marriage and procreation.
"
</P>
<P>
As the capital of the world's most populated country, Beijing
now has a yearly birth rate of 0.65 percent and a population
growth rate of 0.09 percent.
</P>
<P>
Beijing plans to control its population to 11.1 million this
year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
