<DOCNO> XIE20000522.0310 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-05-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing Issues Regulations on Street Committee Election </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 22 (Xinhua) -- Regulations on street committee
elections have been issued by the municipal government of Beijing,
which will go into effect as of June 1, this year.
</P>
<P>
Street committees are self-managed, self-service organizations
made up of urban residents. They play an important role in China's
political, economic, cultural and social affairs as well as in
people's daily life in urban areas.
</P>
<P>
According to the regulations, street committee members should
be selected by the residents themselves through either direct or
indirect elections.
</P>
<P>
The election should be open and no government officials may
randomly dismiss or replace elected street committee members, the
regulations said.
</P>
<P>
China now has more than 117,000 street committees. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
