<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, May 21 (Xinhua) -- Axel Merckx, son of Belgian cycling
legend Eddy Merckx, won the longest stage of the Giro d'Italia on
Sunday after fighting back from a crash.
</P>
<P>
As he finished the 265 kilometers eighth stage from Corinaldo
to Prato, Merckx's father, who won his fifth Giro 26 years ago,
was commentating for television.
</P>
<P>
