<HEADLINE> OAS Observation Tasks in Peru Suspended </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
According to a communique, OAS's mission "has disposed for its
observers to temporarily suspend election observation related with
Office of Electoral Processes (ONPE)", due to "lack of consistency
and precision" of Peruvian election authorities.
</P>
<P>
Peru's President and presidential candidate Alberto Fujimori
and his adversary Alejandro Toledo were scheduled to hold their
run-off election on May 28.
</P>
<P>
Fujimori fell only 20,000 votes short of an outright win in an
April 9 first round, putting him into a run-off with Toledo.
</P>
