<HEADLINE> Mexican President Praises Panama Canal Transfer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, May 22 (Xinhua) --  Mexican President Ernesto
Zedillo Monday told his visiting Panamanian counterpart Mireya
Moscoso that the Canal's transfer was a far-reaching act for Latin
America crowning a long fight of Panama's people.
</P>
<P>
"We Mexicans admire and support at all time Panama people's
patriotism, its invincible decision to assure its nation's full
autonomy", said Zedillo at Los Pinos Presidential Residence, in
Mexico's capital.
</P>
<P>
United States delivered to Panama last December control of this
inter-oceanic way in accordance with the Torrijos-Carter treaties
signed by both countries in 1997.
</P>
<P>
On Monday, Mexico's head of state gave welcome to Moscoso, who
arrived Mexico Sunday for a State visit that will end May 24.
</P>
<P>
Mexico's President expressed to Moscoso how convenient it is
for Mexico and Panama to renew talks for a free trade accord
between both countires, canceled following Moscoso's coming to
power, on September 1, 1999.
</P>
<P>
At the end of the welcoming ceremony, Zedillo and Moscoso
examined bilateral, regional and world matters, as well as diverse
cooperation accords in tourism, trade, education and the
environment.
</P>
<P>
Moscoso has planned to meet Mexico's capital's legislative
authorities and entrepreneurs of both countries in Monterrey,
capital of Nuevo Leon state.
</P>
</TEXT>
