<HEADLINE> Colombia Flood Victims Rise to 14 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BOGOTA, May 22 (Xinhua) -- The number of persons losing their
lives went up to 14 Monday, while 16 disappeared, due to intense
rains that burst several river banks in Colombia.
</P>
<P>
Rains have left nearly 5,000 victims, affecting over a hundred
dwellings and leaving in state of emergency this region's main
urban center.
</P>
<P>
Director of Office of Disaster Prevention and Attention,
Eduardo Jose Gonzalez, said Monday that several towns in this area
and of Putumayo, bordering Ecuador and Peru, as well as Giron, in
Santander, were also affected by the downpours.
</P>
<P>
Gonzalez said that the majority of deaths caused by the storm
happened in Narino, where 13 people lost their lives. 
</P>
</TEXT>
